crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a botnet client, likely a variant of the Mirai (Sofia) family. It propagates by scanning random IP addresses and exploiting a TR-064 command injection vulnerability in Huawei routers (CVE-2014-8361). It crafts a malicious SOAP request to the '/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1' endpoint, using a command injection in the '<NewStatusURL>' field to force the victim device to download and execute a payload with 'wget'. The sample also contains a Telnet brute-force module for further propagation and disables the watchdog timer ('/dev/watchdog') to prevent reboots on infected devices.
